title: "Learn"
:::

# Transformations and composition

If $y=f(x)$, then:

- $f(x)+k$ shifts vertically by $k$;
- $f(x-h)$ shifts right by $h$;
- $af(x)$ scales vertically by $a$;
- $f(bx)$ scales horizontally.

![Two vertical translations of a parabola](../../../assets/images/function-transformations.svg)

Composition is

$$
(f\circ g)(x)=f(g(x)).
$$


> **Study habit:** translate every formula into a sentence about quantities and units.

:::mcf-end

